<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1005" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1005">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1485</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Mayer</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 147</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 167
                            of the 7th ultimo in which you enclose a copy of a memorandum handed to
                            you by Rear Admiral Knapp upon the subject of the relations between
                            treaty officials of the Haitian Government.</p>
                        <p>The Department approves Admiral Knapp’s memorandum and concurs in the
                            views which he has expressed therein.</p>
                        <p>Copies of your despatch and its enclosure have been forwarded to the
                            Secretary of the Navy with this Department’s comment thereon as
                            above.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>